easytidy_converter — third-party components
================================================

This crate builds the native library easytidy_converter.dll used by EasyTidyPro
for file/format conversion. It combines the following third-party components.

Native libraries linked into easytidy_converter.dll
----------------------------------------------------
HEIC/HEIF image decoding (Windows, statically linked):

  - libheif 1.21.2   LGPL-3.0   Copyright (c) struktur AG and contributors
                     https://github.com/strukturag/libheif
  - libde265 1.0.18  LGPL-3.0   Copyright (c) struktur AG and contributors
                     https://github.com/strukturag/libde265
  - aom 3.13.3       BSD-2-Clause   Copyright (c) 2016, Alliance for Open Media
                     https://aomedia.googlesource.com/aom/

Only the decoder path is built. The HEVC/H.265 encoder (x265, GPL-2.0) is
deliberately excluded, so no GPL-2.0 code is distributed.

On non-Windows targets, libheif is compiled from embedded sources via the
libheif-rs `embedded-libheif` feature (still LGPL-3.0).

Rust crate dependencies
-----------------------
Built on top of open-source Rust crates under permissive licenses (primarily
MIT and Apache-2.0), including (non-exhaustive): image, webp, libheif-rs,
typst, comrak, docx-rs, calamine, rust_xlsxwriter, pdfium-render, pdf_oxide,
anyhow, thiserror, log. See Cargo.toml / Cargo.lock and each crate's own
repository for the authoritative license terms.

pdfium.dll (Google PDFium, BSD-3-Clause) is used for PDF rasterization.

